      "writtenOn": "2019-08-16T21:15:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Our style would not be to log the name of the function logging the error, but the name of the function that returned the error. Stylistically, we’d normally move logging up into where you call inflateInit() or deflateInit() above. For example:\n\n  if (mode \u003d\u003d Mode::kDecompress) {\n    res \u003d inflateInit(\u0026zlib_stream_);\n    if (res !\u003d Z_OK) {\n      LOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"inflateInit: \" \u003c\u003c zlib_stream_.msg;\n      return;\n    }\n  } else {\n    // …\n\nBUT: if infliateInit() or deflateInit() fail, zlib_stream_ is not valid. In this case, unlike most other zlib calls, you can’t actually use zlib_stream_.msg at all.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 81,
        "startChar": 19,
        "endLine": 81,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "7438e06f309a431d675c1b81e75fc31071f20d2b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
