      "writtenOn": "2019-08-17T01:50:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e We need a little bit hack here\n\nDon’t be so quick to reach for a hack. Or for a style guide violation.\n\nMost style rules exist for a reason, even if the reasons aren’t immediately apparent.\n\n\u003e using c++ style can\u0027t cast const to non-const, I will add comment here.\n\nTe correct solution when you need to cast for two reasons is to use two casts. If you search the Crashpad source code for cast.*cast, you’ll find numerous hits. You shouldn’t find any C-style casts.\n\nBecause C-style casts are so powerful, they’re more dangerous. If the types involved change, a C-style cast won’t let you know if the types of cast operations performed have become riskier. C++-style casts, because they are explicit, will result in an error in this case, allowing the programmer to consider proper handling.",
      "parentUuid": "2dcbaa0d_66b94345",
      "revId": "7438e06f309a431d675c1b81e75fc31071f20d2b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
